<HEAD>Convicted Child Killer Presses Final Appeal As Execution Looms</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 6 grafs to UPDATE with Supreme Court rejecting Adams'
appeal; picks up 5th graf pvs: `Adams, 31, ...</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RON WORD</BYLINE>
<UNK>Associated Press</UNK>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> refused Wednesday to stay the execution of a convicted child killer scheduled to die Thursday morning, after his attorneys lost similar appeals in three lower courts. The emergency request by <PERSON> Aubrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Adams </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> was denied by the high court in a 7-2 vote. The justices also turned down his formal appeal to review his death sentence. Justices <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> and <PERSON> Thurgood </PERSON> <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON>, who oppose the death penalty in all circumstances, voted to spare <PERSON> Adams </PERSON>. Earlier Wednesday, the 11th U.S. <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> denied a request for a stay of execution for <PERSON> Adams </PERSON>, saying it did n't `` find merit in any of the claims raised.'' The 11th Circuit's decision Wednesday night followed rejection of <PERSON> Adams </PERSON>' appeal by the <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in the morning and by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> II in the afternoon. The <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> appeal was filed in anticipation of the lower court rejections, said <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Spalding </PERSON>, head of the state agency that handles final appeals for inmates facing execution. <PERSON> Adams </PERSON>, 31, a former officer at <ORGANIZATION> Marion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Correctional </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institution </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Ocala </LOCATION>, was origin