the artist's close friend, <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Dyer </PERSON>, sold for $ 5.7 million. Five sculptures by <PERSON> Claes </PERSON> <PERSON> Oldenburg </PERSON> were sold: `` Ice Cream Sandwich,'' $ 370,000; `` Plate of Meat,'' $ 360,000; `` Bacon and Egg,'' $ 450,000; `` Cheesecake from Javatime,'' $ 47,500; and `` Green Beans,'' $ 240,000. <PERSON> Andy </PERSON> <PERSON> Warhol </PERSON>'s `` Red <PERSON> Jackie </PERSON>,'' which portrays a ruby-lipped <PERSON> Jacqueline </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> <PERSON> Onassis </PERSON> as first lady in 1963, sold for $ 750,000 _ more than twice the presale estimate. `` Red <PERSON> Marilyn </PERSON>,'' a 1964 depiction of <PERSON> Marilyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Monroe </PERSON>, will be offered at <PERSON> Christie </PERSON>'s on Wednesday. The estimate for the signed, synthetic polymer silkscreen on canvas is $ 1.5 million to $ 2 million. Other <PERSON> Christie </PERSON>'s offerings include `` Colored Alphabet,'' a 12-by-10 -LCB- inch oil and paper collage by <PERSON> Jasper </PERSON> <PERSON> Johns </PERSON>, estimated at $ 1.5 million. The theme `` is, in fact, the alphabet. But it's in vivid, overlapping colors: various shades of blue, yellow and red with some black,'' said <PERSON> Roberta </PERSON> <PERSON> Maneker </PERSON>, a <PERSON> Christie </PERSON>'s spokeswoman. A Sotheby sale next Tuesday features <PERSON> Gauguin </PERSON>'s `` Mata Mua,'' circa 1892, completed during the artist's first trip to <LOCATION> Tahiti </LOCATION>. Estimated at $ 20 million to $ 25 million, it is being sold by <PERSON> Jaime </PERSON> <PERSON> Ortiz-Patino </PERSON>, heir to a Bolivian tin fortune, and <PERSON> Baron </PERSON> <PERSON> Hans </PERSON> <PERSON> Heinrich </PERSON> <PERSON> Thyssen-Bornemisza </PERSON>, a member of the advisory board of <ORGANIZATION> Sotheby </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION>. The same day, `` <PERSON> Yo </PERSON> <PERSON> Pi