s that she went on shopping binges, disbursing thousands of dollars on jewelry, designer clothes, paintings; whatever captured her fancy,'' he wrote. After the August 1963 death of the <PERSON> Kennedys </PERSON>' third child, when the boy was just 3 days old, the couple seemed to grow closer in their grief, <PERSON> Heymann </PERSON> wrote. But Mrs. <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>'s life was shattered on Nov. 22, 1963, in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> when her husband was assassinated while riding with her in a motorcade. <PERSON> Heymann </PERSON> wrote that the first lady refused to take a sedative as she waited in her blood-splattered outfit at Parkland Memorial Hospital. `` I do n't want a sedative,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> reportedly said. `` I want to be with my husband when he dies.''
