LOCATION>. The radio complained that the government had changed its outer shell but `` the true nature remains a Vietnamese puppet, socialist regime.'' In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Tutwiler </PERSON> said Tuesday that close ties with a future Cambodian government would not be possible if it were heavily influenced by the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON> said the Sino-Soviet summit in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> in mid-May should be beneficial to his cause. He said Soviet President <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> `` may put some moral pressure on Hun Sen'' and the <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> leadership might apply pressure on the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> to seek a settlement in the 10-year-old conflict. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> is the primary military backer of the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION>.
