<TEXT>
 Premier <PERSON> Ruud </PERSON> <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON> formally submitted the resignation of his seven-year coalition government Wednesday, and early elections are being scheduled for Sept. 6 or 13, the government announced. Elections had not been due until May 1990. The announcement followed a 90-minute visit by <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON> to Queen <PERSON> Beatrix </PERSON> late Wednesday, his second of the day, and talks between the monarch and the leaders of all nine political parties represented in <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION>. In his first meeting, <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON> submitted the resignation of his entire 13-minister, center-right Cabinet in a clash over part of a $ 3.65 billion plan to clean up the heavily polluted Dutch environment by the year 2010. The plan came under heavy fire from the right-wing <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Freedom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democracy </ORGANIZATION>, junior partner in his government since 1982 It objected to <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON>' proposal to end certain income tax deductions for Dutch commuters who daily drive long distances to and from work. The party threatened a no-confidence motion, precipitating the government's fall. <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON>' Cabinet will stay on as caretaker until a new government is formed. Political observers predict <PERSON> Lubbers </PERSON>, of the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> party </ORGANIZATION>, will drop the <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Freedom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democracy </ORGANIZATION> in a new coalition tha