<HEAD>Thousand Salute Indicted Wall Street Wizard for Charity Donations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GEORGE GARTIES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Indicted financier <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> was honored Wednesday for multimillion-dollar donations to charity at a celebrity-studded lunch sponsored by a group that helps children. <PERSON> Milken </PERSON>, who lost his job as top bond trader for <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> because of his alleged role in a staggering securities-fraud scandal, was praised as one who gives unstintingly _ not just with money but his own time. He also has become a personal friend of many children aided by the H.E.L.P. group, said the organization's founder, <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Firestone </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> is the kind of guy who is always giving and not demanding anything in return,'' Ms. <PERSON> Firestone </PERSON> said at the lunch. <PERSON> Milken </PERSON>, one of the nation's most dynamic and wealthy financiers, was indicted March 29 on 98 federal counts of racketeering, fraud and stock manipulation stemming largely from the confessions of now-imprisoned insider trader <PERSON> Ivan </PERSON> <PERSON> Boesky </PERSON>. Charged along with <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> are his brother, <PERSON> Lowell </PERSON>, and <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> trader <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Newberg </PERSON>. All have asserted their innocence and vowed to fight the charges. Before his appearance at the Beverly Hilton Hotel lunch, <PERSON> Milken </PERSON>, who has portrayed himself as the target of overzealous prosecutors, told a reporter who asked about his public image: `` What you see here is reality.'' Among the approximately 1,000 attending the luncheon were comedian <PERSON> Whoopi </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldberg </PERSON>, actor <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Weaver </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> baseball manager <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lasorda </PERSON> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> state Controller <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>. The gathering was held in the same ballroom used for the `` Predators Ball,'' an annual <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> conference on the value of junk bonds. <PERSON> Milken </PERSON>, credited with creating the multibillion-dollar market in those high-yield, high-risk bonds, missed this year's Predators Ball a few weeks ago for the first time in 10 years because of his legal problems H.E.L.P. provides group homes for children who have physical, mental or emotional problems.
